 3 May\n|date=3 May 2020|via=BBC}}</ref>\n|-\n! Total || 3,767 || 381 || 29,629* || 3,829* ||\n|}\n\n*Total amount of tests will not add up to the total of daily tests listed above as test numbers are not always announced on a daily basis, however when they are a new overall total is announced as well.\n*Some data is taken from the Department of Health COVID-19 dashboard which updates daily. \n*The data for recovered cases is taken from daily updates from the Department of Health regarding hospital discharges. This data is a combination of suspected and confirmed COVID-19 cases in hospitals so it may be a larger figure than confirmed cases.\n\n==See also==\n* [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United Kingdom]]\n** [[COVID-19 pandemic in England]]\n** [[COVID-19 pandemic in Scotland]]\n** [[COVID-19 pandemic in Wales]]\n** [[COVID-19 pandemic in London]]\n* [[COVID-19 pandemic in the Republic of Ireland]]\n* [[Caroline McElnay]], the [[County Antrim]] native directing [[COVID-19 pandemic in New Zealand|New Zealand]]'s battle against the virus\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\nhttps://files.nisra.gov.uk/Births,%20Deaths%20and%20Marriages/Weekly-Deaths-Dashboard.html\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite news|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/meet-the-irish-woman-near-the-top-of-new-zealand-s-covid-19-response-1.4224223|title=Meet the Irish woman near the top of New Zealand's Covid-19 response: Our advantage is that we are an island nation' \u2013 Dr Caroline McElnay|first=Mike|last=Milotte|date=9 April 2020|work=[[The Irish Times]]|location=[[Auckland]]}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/coronavirus-covid-19/ Coronavirus (COVID-19) on the NHS website]\n* [https://www.gov.uk/government/topical-events/coronavirus-covid-19-uk-government-response Coronavirus (COVID-19): UK government response]\n* [https://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2020/129/contents/made The Health Protection (Coronavirus) Regulations 2020]. Legislation.gov.uk\n* [https://www